<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Flowering and fruiting times from July to September.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="etymology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
The specific epithet 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">vanchingshanensis</emphasis>
is derived from the type locality 
<normalizedToken originalValue="“Vanchingshan”">&quot;Vanchingshan&quot;</normalizedToken>
, a variant name for Fanjingshan Mountain.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Y. Wu ex Huan C. Wang &amp; Feng Yang" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene vanchingshanensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vanchingshanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Silene vanchingshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">locus classicus</emphasis>
(Fanjingshan Mountain), a famous scenic resort in Guizhou, southwest China. The species grows on cliffs or rock crevices of the mountain summit at elevations of 2,100-2,500 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="155" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Y. Wu ex Huan C. Wang &amp; Feng Yang" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene vanchingshanensis" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vanchingshanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Silene vanchingshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first proposed by the Chinese botanist Zhengyi Wu in 1988 on the label of a KUN specimen (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">C. P. Jian et al. 32080</emphasis>
). However, no name was formally published.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
According to the taxonomic treatment of Chinese 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Silene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Tang, CL" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Biology" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" refId="B15" refString="Tang, CL, 1994. Three new section of Chinese Silene. Acta Botanica Yunnanica 16(2): 117-119." title="Three new section of Chinese Silene. Acta Botanica Yunnanica 16 (2): 117 - 119." year="1994">Tang (1994)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. vanchingshanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="vanchingshanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">S. vanchingshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be assigned to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene subsp. sect." order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Morrisonmontanae" species="vanchingshanensis" subSpecies="sect.">Silene sect. Morrisonmontanae</taxonomicName>
C. L. Tang (synonymised in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Silene" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Silene subsp. sect." order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Physolychnis" species="vanchingshanensis" subSpecies="sect.">Silene sect. Physolychnis</taxonomicName>
(Benth.) Bocquet in 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12230" author="Jafari, F" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" pagination="337 - 368" refId="B8" refString="Jafari, F, Zarre, S, Gholipour, A, Eggens, F, Rabeler, RK, Oxelman, B, 2020. A new taxonomic backbone for the infrageneric classification of the species rich genus Silene (Caryophyllaceae). Taxon 69 (2): 337 - 368, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12230" title="A new taxonomic backbone for the infrageneric classification of the species rich genus Silene (Caryophyllaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12230" volume="69" year="2020">Jafari et al. (2020)</bibRefCitation>
) due to its cymes 2-5-flowered and campanulate calyx. 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. vanchingshanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="vanchingshanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">S. vanchingshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is mostly similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. morrisonmontana" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="morrisonmontana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">S. morrisonmontana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hayata) Ohwi &amp; H.Ohashi, but differs from the latter by its leaves linear-oblanceolate (vs. linear), 3-6 cm 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-6 mm (vs. 2-7 cm 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm), cymes (1-) 2-5-flowered (vs. usually solitary) and petals pink or violet (vs. white). The distribution areas of these two species are separated: 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. vanchingshanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="vanchingshanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">S. vanchingshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Guizhou, while 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. morrisonmontana" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="morrisonmontana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">S. morrisonmontana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only found in Taiwan. 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. vanchingshanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="vanchingshanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">S. vanchingshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. hupehensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="hupehensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">S. hupehensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
C. L. Tang, but clearly differs from the latter by its stems with hairs, 10-15 cm (vs. glabrous, 10-30 cm) long, leaves linear-oblanceolate (vs. narrowly linear), 3-6 cm 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-6 mm (vs. 5-8 cm 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3.5 mm) and capsule narrowly ovoid (vs. ovoid), 12-15 mm (vs. 6-8 mm) long. A detailed morphological comparison between these three species is summarised in Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Morphological comparison of S. vanchingshanensis, S. morrisonmontana and S. hupehensis." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/C0A813DE32FDB6C33AD3A110BC865580" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" tableUuid="C0A813DE32FDB6C33AD3A110BC865580">1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Table-UUID="C0A813DE32FDB6C33AD3A110BC865580" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/C0A813DE32FDB6C33AD3A110BC865580" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" start="Table 1" startId="T1">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="155">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">Table 1.</emphasis>
Morphological comparison of 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. vanchingshanensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="vanchingshanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">S. vanchingshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. morrisonmontana" pageId="0" pageNumber="155" rank="species" species="morrisonmontana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="155">S. morrisonmontana</emphasis>
